# Git: push to main after updates

When you finish a meaningful code update in this repo (feature, fix, or refactor the user cares to test):

1. Stage the relevant files (`git add`).
2. Commit with a clear message (what changed and why).
3. Push to **`main`**: `git push origin main`.

Do this as part of the same task unless the user explicitly asks not to push or to use a branch/PR. If push fails (auth, remote), report the error and suggest fixes.

Do not skip push when the user wants live testing on Netlify/hosting tied to `main`.
